I think that the native app creates own subshell and progress bar redraw its output. This example has to work:
```powershell
& {
     for ($i = 5; $i -gt 0; $i–-) {
         Write-Progress -Activity "Launching rocket" -SecondsRemaining $i
         Start-Sleep 1
          #  Write-Host $(cmd /c ver)
         $(cmd /c ver)
     }
     Write-Host "Output messed up!" -Fore Yellow
 }
```
